A museum dedicated to the actor-politician. He lived with his family in the modest first floor flat from his birth in 1947 until 1966 when he left to pursue his dreams of winning the Mr Universe competition. The building, built in 1806, is the former forester's lodge of the counts Herberstein or Eggenberg.
